# Wiki Primary Memory Default

## Main rule

- Treat `secondbrain/knowledge/*` and `secondbrain/knowledge/project-context.md` as default project memory in every session.
- Assume this memory is active context unless the user explicitly asks for a deep fresh audit.

## Token-efficiency behavior

- Do not repeatedly re-scan the whole repository for topics already captured in wiki.
- Do not repeatedly re-scan the whole wiki for the same topic in one work cycle.
- Use targeted file reads only when exact implementation details or line-accurate edits are required.

## Decision policy

- For architecture, bugfix strategy, feature planning, and trade-offs: start from wiki concepts/connections first.
- Use codebase scanning only to:
  - confirm current implementation details,
  - resolve ambiguity/conflicts,
  - perform concrete edits safely.

## Update policy

- If a request introduces durable changes (architecture, invariants, security, cache, protocol, core patterns), persist updates to wiki in the same cycle.
- Keep updates concise and non-noisy; avoid wiki churn for trivial edits.

